description: Ibrutinib is an irreversible small-molecule tyrosine kinase inhibitor of BTK that is NCCN-listed and FDA-approved for adult patients with chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL)/small lymphocytic lymphoma (SLL) with or without 17p deletion. In a study of 308 patients with CLL who enrolled in four sequential clinical trials of ibrutinib, one patient had a C481F mutation at disease progression with a variant allele frequency of 84% (PMID: 27282255, 26182309).
